news.title: Mushrooming of illegal colonies across country is menace to urban development: SC
news.para: "Mushrooming of illegal colonies in all these cities in this country, the consequences are so drastic. We have seen floods in Hyderabad and Kerala, all this is because of irregular colonies.

news.title: British Land sells majority stake in Paddington Central assets to GIC for $886 million
news.para: Commercial landlords have struggled over the past two years as multiple COVID lockdowns and an extended moratorium on rent collection has hurt retail-focused assets, while a shift to remote working has weighed on office portfolios.

news.title: Greater Noida development body rolls out one-time scheme till September
news.para: Under the scheme, the allottees will now have to pay a lesser amount for defaulting on the premium. Defaulters, officials said, will have to pay a simple interest on a defaulted amount, and not a compound interest that is usually charged.

news.title: NCLAT directs no further steps in insolvency case against Santasha Real Estate
news.para: ​The New Delhi bench of the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) had on March 29, 2022 ordered for initiation of insolvency proceedings against the realty firm over a plea filed by Vani Advertising, an operational creditor to the company, claiming default.

news.title: Shriram Properties to sell up to 90 acre land in Kolkata to Logos
news.para: The MoU for the proposed transaction was signed at the Global Investor Summit organised by the West Bengal government in Kolkata, and is subject to necessary due-diligence and certain regulatory approvals.

news.title: Rajasthan builders can register projects by March 31
news.para: The RERA issued an order giving relaxation to the builders on getting the registration of the ongoing projects which was valid till March 31, 2022. This period has now been extended by RERA for one year till March 31, 2023.

news.title: BHEL to raze 2,400 dilapidated quarters
news.para: Constructed almost 60 years ago, the BHEL quarters were once a famous residential colony in Bhopal. Gradually, these houses were abandoned after several employees retired and started living outside the township.

news.title: As more flats come up in Delhi-NCR, residents' body writes to minister on drinking water
news.para: The association, in the letter, demanded increased water supply through canals, rivers and natural sources and suggested that a proper policy should be drawn up for mandatory water harvesting at all government establishments, such as administrative offices, bungalows, stadiums, bus terminals, railway stations, airports to colleges, schools etc.

news.title: Delhi high street gets premium tag back
news.para: Rentals at the two Delhi retail hubs have increased by 16.7% year-on-year in the first quarter of 2022, surpassing pre-Covid levels, as per real estate consultancy Cushman & Wakefield.

news.title: Bengaluru: Nadaprabhu Kempegowda Layout allottees yet to get sites registered
news.para: Nadaprabhu Kempegowda Layout allottees claim authority’s work is shoddy, slow; many are yet to get sites registered despite payments, follow-ups

news.title: Chandigarh administration demolishes over 100 illegal structures in Manimajra
news.para: UT staff demolished more than 100 illegal temporary structures. The demolition drive was conducted with the UT police department and SDM office.

news.title: NCDRC orders Kapstone Constructions to refund buyer's money with interest for delayed flat
news.para: It ordered Kapstone Constructions Pvt Ltd to pay around Rs 63 lakh in interest and refund Rs 1.17 crore to flat buyers Anuj and Somara Biswas.

news.title: About 131% rise in registration for new projects, mostly from rural Madhya Pradesh
news.para: Since the establishment of RERA years back, a maximum 558 applications have been received for registration in the financial year 2021-2022.

news.title: Seven years on, SEIAA has not decided on green & parking spaces in Mulund project: NGT
news.para: The tribunal order said, “Thus, the status of EC remains that of “deemed inoperative”. The PP (project proponent) stands restrained from carrying out any further work till the issue is decided by SEIAA in terms of order of this Tribunal.’’

news.title: Kumar Mangalam Birla weighs ACC, Ambuja bid, move may invite regulator scrutiny
news.para: Birla's flagship UltraTech is the leading cement player in the country and any bid will face scrutiny from India's anti-trust watchdog. UltraTech's capacity, combined with that of Ambuja Cement and ACC Ltd, the two listed arms of The Holcim Group in India, will reach dominant market share in some states.
